OL,6,FAt Grimsby Crown Court, Senior Crown
OL,7,FAdvocate, Jeremy Evans said Mr Simons
OL,8,Fwas an enthusiastic and proficient
OL,9,Fcyclist. He was wearing a backpack
OL,10,Fwith a reflective covering and his
OL,11,Fspecialist cycle was fitted with
OL,12,Fstrobe red lighting at the rear and a
OL,13,Flight at the front. He also wore a
OL,14,Fsafety helmet.JHe commuted 17 miles to
OL,15,FImmingham from his home in each
OL,16,Fworkday, he said. Mr Simons was
OL,17,Fpositioned correctly on the uphill
OL,18,Fclimb out of South Ferriby towards
OL,19,FBarton and had been seen by other
OL,20,Fmotorists.JBut Parker, driving a Ford
OL,21,FKuga, did not see the rider and struck
OL,22,Fthe rear of the cycle. Mr Evans said a
OL,23,Fpolice reconstruction of the collision
OL,24,Fshowed the driver had 24 seconds to
OL,25,Fsee the cyclist before the impact.JThe
OL,26,Fstretch of the A1077 is governed by a
